                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d871">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/6995: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-02T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 2, 1939—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>215. Department’s 197, October 19, 8 p.m., foreign personnel of the Chinese
                    Government Salt Administration. It is suggested that the information contained
                    in Shanghai’s despatch no. 2532, September 15, 1939, and its enclosures may be
                    of use in connection with your approaches to the Chinese.</p>
                <p>Sent to Chungking. Repeated to Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
